WEBVTT

00:01.302 --> 00:01.469
.

00:01.502 --> 00:02.670
- In the criminal justice
system, sexually based offenses

00:05.106 --> 00:06.540
are considered
especially heinous.

00:06.574 --> 00:09.277
In New York City,
the dedicated detectives

00:09.310 --> 00:11.112
who investigate
these vicious felonies

00:11.145 --> 00:12.480
are members of an elite squad

00:12.513 --> 00:14.415
known as
the Special Victims Unit.

00:14.448 --> 00:17.285
These are their stories.

00:17.318 --> 00:19.287
[screaming]

00:19.320 --> 00:20.554
- It's a hate crime.

00:20.588 --> 00:22.390
- I saw his face.

00:22.423 --> 00:24.125
He took his mask off
for a few seconds.

00:24.158 --> 00:25.459
- Hector Ramirez.
You come clean,

00:25.493 --> 00:27.128
you tell us
who the other two guys were,

00:27.161 --> 00:28.796
you might be able
to cut yourself a deal.

00:28.829 --> 00:30.598
- I didn't kill or rape anyone,
I swear to God.

00:30.631 --> 00:32.466
- What do I need to do?

00:32.500 --> 00:33.567
- Need to testify
in front of grand jury

00:33.601 --> 00:35.169
so we can formally indict him.

00:35.203 --> 00:36.504
- Oh, no.

00:36.537 --> 00:37.838
- Hey,
what the hell are you doing?

00:37.871 --> 00:39.207
- He's being deported to Syria.

00:39.240 --> 00:40.408
- Two people were killed,

00:40.441 --> 00:41.642
and you're deporting
the one person

00:41.675 --> 00:43.511
that can ID the men
that did this?

00:43.544 --> 00:44.645
- The people have just released
Hector Ramirez.

00:44.678 --> 00:46.614
- He won't be free for long.

00:46.647 --> 00:49.250
- The release today of Samra
double homicide suspect

00:49.283 --> 00:52.153
Hector Ramirez
has galvanized civil unrest

00:52.186 --> 00:53.854
outside the courthouse.

00:53.887 --> 00:55.656
Members of the Muslim
and Latino communities

00:55.689 --> 00:58.859
are out in force...
- You guys all right?

00:58.892 --> 01:01.229
- For the most part.
- Wasn't pretty.

01:01.262 --> 01:04.265
- Unfortunately, your day's not
getting any easier.

01:04.298 --> 01:08.269
- What now?
- Maya and Lela Samra are here.

01:08.302 --> 01:11.505
Yeah.

01:11.539 --> 01:13.307
- No, I-I don't understand.

01:13.341 --> 01:16.577
You promised me
that Yusef would be safe,

01:16.610 --> 01:18.846
that New York
is a sanctuary city--

01:18.879 --> 01:22.616
- And I am so sorry.
- No, no, this is on me.

01:22.650 --> 01:24.452
I never should have let him
leave the apartment.

01:24.485 --> 01:27.355
- No, no. Yusef is stubborn.
He wanted cigarettes.

01:27.388 --> 01:31.192
- But he needs to testify.
He's our most important witness.

01:31.225 --> 01:34.362
You said that the D.A.
was getting a warrant.

01:34.395 --> 01:37.498
- By the time we found out
where Yusef was being held,

01:37.531 --> 01:39.267
it was too late.

01:39.300 --> 01:43.337
He was already on
a plane headed to Syria.

01:43.371 --> 01:45.373
- So get him back.

01:47.175 --> 01:49.377
- I have to be honest with you.

01:49.410 --> 01:52.480
I don't know if that's possible.

01:52.513 --> 01:56.184
- So he's just gone?

01:56.217 --> 01:58.719
- And Hector gets to go free?

01:58.752 --> 02:01.722
Like the rapes and murders
never happened?

02:01.755 --> 02:03.157
- Listen to me.

02:03.191 --> 02:04.525
We are gonna find them.

02:04.558 --> 02:06.227
And we are gonna prosecute them.

02:06.260 --> 02:09.697
We are not giving up
on this case.

02:09.730 --> 02:13.234
- Liv, we have a situation.

02:13.267 --> 02:15.536
- Excuse me.
What?

02:15.569 --> 02:18.439
[sirens wailing]
- Move in! Move in! Move in!

02:18.472 --> 02:21.442
[dramatic music]

02:21.475 --> 02:23.244
*

02:23.277 --> 02:26.247
[police radio chatter]

02:26.280 --> 02:29.417
- Lieutenant Benson, SVU.
Hector Ramirez inside?

02:29.450 --> 02:31.352
- Being held at gunpoint.
- By who?

02:31.385 --> 02:33.387
- Witnesses say two males,
20s, Middle Eastern.

02:33.421 --> 02:35.389
- Do we know what they want?
- No. Hostage negotiation's

02:35.423 --> 02:37.325
been calling the bar's landline;
they're not picking up.

02:37.358 --> 02:38.759
- Anybody else inside?
- No, they let

02:38.792 --> 02:40.728
all the employees,
rest of the patrons go.

02:40.761 --> 02:43.964
Just the three of them.
We're setting up pole cams now.

02:43.997 --> 02:45.666
See if we can isolate
the hostage takers.

02:45.699 --> 02:48.602
- Okay, I cannot risk
this witness getting killed.

02:48.636 --> 02:50.671
- We're on the same page.
Last thing we want

02:50.704 --> 02:52.573
is to lose a hostage.
- I understand that

02:52.606 --> 02:55.209
but this witness is different.
- We'll try to negotiate.

02:55.243 --> 02:57.345
But if we get a clear shot,
we're gonna take it.

02:57.378 --> 02:58.546
- Ugh!
- Come on.

02:58.579 --> 03:01.549
[police radio chatter]

03:01.582 --> 03:03.317
[phone ringing]
- Aakif, there's a lot

03:03.351 --> 03:04.318
of cops out there--
- Good! They should know

03:04.352 --> 03:05.553
we're serious.

03:05.586 --> 03:07.255
Who killed Kanann
and Shala Samra?

03:07.288 --> 03:08.556
- It wasn't me.
I didn't hurt them.

03:08.589 --> 03:11.225
- Then who did?
[phone ringing]

03:11.259 --> 03:14.295
- Should I pick it up?
- No!

03:14.328 --> 03:16.397
- They gave you a job.
They looked out for you.

03:16.430 --> 03:18.799
This is how you repay them?

03:18.832 --> 03:20.734
- You have a visual
in the back window.

03:20.768 --> 03:23.337
Are you seeing it?

03:23.371 --> 03:26.374
- Copy.
I have a clear shot.

03:26.407 --> 03:28.242
- Take it now.
- Just wait.

03:28.276 --> 03:29.677
- [grunts]
- Ohh!

03:29.710 --> 03:31.245
- Move, move, move!

03:31.279 --> 03:33.814
- Shots fired!
Shots fired!

03:33.847 --> 03:35.783
- No! Aakif, no!
- Police! Let me see your hands!

03:35.816 --> 03:38.652
- No, no!
The Samras are good people!

03:38.686 --> 03:42.356
We just wanted justice--
- All right, get him back here.

03:42.390 --> 03:44.592
- Hector.
- They were gonna kill me!

03:44.625 --> 03:46.727
- Yeah, well, they didn't.
- Get him out of here.

03:46.760 --> 03:48.362
[police radio chatter]

03:48.396 --> 03:55.436
*

03:59.039 --> 04:02.009
[dramatic music]

04:48.322 --> 04:48.489
.

04:48.522 --> 04:49.056
- They were gonna shoot me.

04:50.491 --> 04:52.025
I was minding my own business.

04:52.059 --> 04:53.994
- What were you doing
in the bar, Hector?

04:54.027 --> 04:56.364
- Trying to get drunk.
I was locked up for three days.

04:56.397 --> 04:58.366
I wasn't looking for trouble,
I swear.

04:58.399 --> 05:00.033
- What did they want?

05:00.067 --> 05:02.069
- They must've been
following me.

05:02.102 --> 05:04.472
I was having a few beers
and they put a gun to my head

05:04.505 --> 05:07.508
and demanded to know who killed
Kanann and Shala.

05:07.541 --> 05:10.744
I said it wasn't me.
I didn't hurt them.

05:10.778 --> 05:13.347
- You let it happen.

05:13.381 --> 05:16.016
You let those girls get raped.

05:16.049 --> 05:19.620
You let Shala and Kanann die.

05:19.653 --> 05:21.489
- They had--
- You did that.

05:21.522 --> 05:23.624
- They had a gun on me.
- And until you tell us

05:23.657 --> 05:27.661
who else is involved,
this is not going away.

05:27.695 --> 05:29.497
- Hector's lawyer is here.

05:33.701 --> 05:35.135
- What the hell
do you think you're doing?

05:35.168 --> 05:36.970
You can't talk to my client.

05:37.004 --> 05:39.006
- He's a victim in a crime.
- Yes, a victim

05:39.039 --> 05:40.774
who's also facing
a double murder charge.

05:40.808 --> 05:43.477
- He was just telling me
what happened in the bar.

05:43.511 --> 05:44.712
Nothing more.
- He's done talking.

05:44.745 --> 05:46.480
- Okay.
That's your choice.

05:46.514 --> 05:48.782
- And a stupid one, at that.
- Excuse me?

05:48.816 --> 05:51.018
- It's obvious
he wants to cooperate.

05:51.051 --> 05:53.554
- Hector has a rock solid alibi
that his wife will corroborate.

05:53.587 --> 05:56.156
You've got the wrong guy, here.
- So the witness who picked him

05:56.189 --> 05:57.991
out of a lineup--
- Is now in a refugee camp,

05:58.025 --> 05:59.727
somewhere in Turkey.
- And that doesn't mean

05:59.760 --> 06:01.529
that his ID isn't valid.

06:01.562 --> 06:03.564
- I have a client to defend,
and as of right now,

06:03.597 --> 06:05.699
the state doesn't have
enough evidence to convict.

06:05.733 --> 06:09.102
So if you'll excuse me, I'd like
to take Hector to the hospital.

06:09.136 --> 06:10.538
Unless, of course,
you wanna arrest him

06:10.571 --> 06:13.974
for being held hostage.

06:14.007 --> 06:15.543
- [sighs]

06:20.147 --> 06:21.749
Chief.

06:21.782 --> 06:23.717
- What are we looking at?
One dead?

06:23.751 --> 06:25.686
- One of the hostage takers.
- What do we know about 'em?

06:25.719 --> 06:27.455
- The deceased is Aakif Ahmadi.

06:27.488 --> 06:29.189
He's 28, he's
a local business owner.

06:29.222 --> 06:31.191
And the other is Daleel Hamdan.
He's 25.

06:31.224 --> 06:34.528
He's a student at CUNY Tech.
Neither one had a record.

06:34.562 --> 06:36.196
Neither has ties
to terrorist activity.

06:36.229 --> 06:38.098
- As far as we can tell,
it was personal.

06:38.131 --> 06:39.800
Daleel said they were fed up
with the slurs and hatred.

06:39.833 --> 06:41.569
They just wanted to get justice
for the Samras.

06:41.602 --> 06:43.471
- They held Hector at gunpoint
and they demanded

06:43.504 --> 06:45.005
that he reveal
his co-conspirators.

06:45.038 --> 06:46.607
- Did he?
- No.

06:46.640 --> 06:48.609
- His lawyer has him convinced
he's innocent.

06:48.642 --> 06:50.811
- So, look, the wife
is backing up his alibi.

06:50.844 --> 06:53.146
So we need to talk to her and
see if we can crack her story.

06:53.180 --> 06:56.717
- Do it fast.
This needs to end...

06:56.750 --> 06:58.819
before somebody else
gets killed.

07:03.156 --> 07:05.759
- It's your fault.
You arrested Hector.

07:05.793 --> 07:07.227
Made people think
he had something to do

07:07.260 --> 07:09.229
with that horrible crime
at the restaurant.

07:09.262 --> 07:11.164
That's why they wanted
to hurt him.

07:11.198 --> 07:13.233
That's why everyone hates us.

07:13.266 --> 07:16.136
- No, they hate Hector
because he was there.

07:16.169 --> 07:18.171
He was in the restaurant
the night of the attack.

07:18.205 --> 07:19.239
- Says you.

07:19.272 --> 07:21.509
- Says the evidence.

07:21.542 --> 07:24.177
- You don't know what it's like.
I can't leave the apartment.

07:24.211 --> 07:25.746
I can't take the kids outside.

07:25.779 --> 07:27.681
- So work with us, Soledad.
You and Hector.

07:27.715 --> 07:29.783
We can keep you safe.
We can keep your kids safe.

07:29.817 --> 07:31.885
- Hector didn't do
what you say he did.

07:31.919 --> 07:33.587
He was home with me.
- This is not

07:33.621 --> 07:36.156
what's best
for your children.

07:36.189 --> 07:38.125
- You threatening to call
social services again?

07:38.158 --> 07:41.094
- Soledad, all right,
if you get on the stand,

07:41.128 --> 07:43.497
and you lie for your husband,
that's perjury.

07:43.531 --> 07:44.565
That's a crime
- Which means

07:44.598 --> 07:45.766
you could be in trouble.

07:45.799 --> 07:46.800
Which means there's no one here

07:46.834 --> 07:48.168
to look after your kids.

07:48.201 --> 07:49.770
- Stop talking about my kids.

07:49.803 --> 07:52.139
- There's no other way
around it.

07:52.172 --> 07:54.174
You are in
a serious situation here.

07:54.207 --> 07:57.678
- Get out. Get out.

07:57.711 --> 07:59.747
Please get out.

08:02.683 --> 08:03.751
[crowd shouting]

08:03.784 --> 08:05.285
- Ignorance, not immigrants!

08:05.318 --> 08:08.088
NYPD needs to protect
all citizens.

08:08.121 --> 08:09.723
- How many more innocent Muslims
have to die

08:09.757 --> 08:11.592
before NYPD does its job?

08:13.694 --> 08:17.731
- We knew the man who got shot,
Aakif.

08:17.765 --> 08:19.833
- I'm so sorry.

08:19.867 --> 08:21.802
- Why did this have to happen?

08:21.835 --> 08:23.737
- It got out of control.

08:23.771 --> 08:25.272
And he did have a gun.

08:25.305 --> 08:28.676
- Maybe he should have
killed Hector.

08:28.709 --> 08:31.712
- Then we wouldn't know
who the other two men are.

08:31.745 --> 08:34.682
- We need to put pressure
on Hector to cooperate.

08:34.715 --> 08:36.850
And that means
that we need proof.

08:36.884 --> 08:38.886
We need evidence.

08:38.919 --> 08:42.155
So is there any detail? Is there
anything that you can think of?

08:42.189 --> 08:44.558
Anything you can remember
that puts Hector

08:44.592 --> 08:46.860
at the restaurant that night?

08:52.866 --> 08:56.203
- I didn't know it was him.

08:56.236 --> 08:59.873
I didn't recognize his voice.

08:59.907 --> 09:03.611
- Anything?

09:03.644 --> 09:05.979
- One of them,
when they first came in,

09:06.013 --> 09:10.317
he had turned off
the security camera

09:10.350 --> 09:12.219
at the front door.

09:12.252 --> 09:15.623
But he went to it straight away,
like he knew it was there.

09:15.656 --> 09:18.291
- So it could've been Hector.

09:18.325 --> 09:21.895
- Yes. Maybe it was him.

09:21.929 --> 09:23.631
- That's--that's helpful.

09:23.664 --> 09:25.599
That's very helpful.

09:25.633 --> 09:29.169
[solemn music]

09:29.202 --> 09:32.706
- We did find Hector Ramirez's
prints on the security camera.

09:32.740 --> 09:34.642
- Useless.
He worked in the restaurant.

09:34.675 --> 09:36.744
- Yeah, but he was let go
three weeks before the attack.

09:36.777 --> 09:38.378
- Yeah, and he was a bus boy.
He cleared tables.

09:38.411 --> 09:39.813
He wasn't in charge of security.

09:39.847 --> 09:42.215
- Yes, yes, yes.
It's weak evidence.

09:42.249 --> 09:43.851
- Okay, we know.
We all understand.

09:43.884 --> 09:45.686
Let's--let's calm down.

09:45.719 --> 09:48.388
- [sighs]
What about the wife?

09:48.421 --> 09:50.791
She's illegal, right?
- Yeah.

09:53.260 --> 09:55.663
- Let's call ICE.

09:55.696 --> 09:57.264
- Excuse me?

09:57.297 --> 09:59.667
Hold on.
Are we gonna help ICE now

09:59.700 --> 10:01.301
deport a woman
with two little kids?

10:01.334 --> 10:03.270
- I don't know, but we're
certainly gonna threaten it.

10:03.303 --> 10:05.372
- You do remember that New York
is a sanctuary city?

10:05.405 --> 10:06.907
You remember that, right?
- She's lying to protect

10:06.940 --> 10:08.742
a suspect involved
in a horrific crime.

10:08.776 --> 10:10.410
Two people were raped,
two people were killed.

10:10.443 --> 10:13.380
The mother and wife was forced
to watch, to listen.

10:13.413 --> 10:15.683
So call me crazy, Detective.

10:15.716 --> 10:17.685
But in the case of a tie,
my sympathy

10:17.718 --> 10:19.653
is with Maya and Lela,
not with the wife of the perp.

10:19.687 --> 10:20.921
- Lieutenant.
- You're right, Carisi.

10:20.954 --> 10:22.890
That is NYPD's policy.

10:22.923 --> 10:25.959
Absolutely,
we all agree on that.

10:25.993 --> 10:28.028
But this is different.

10:28.061 --> 10:30.230
I'm not a shill for the Feds
and I certainly

10:30.263 --> 10:32.265
don't give a damn about
immigration status.

10:32.299 --> 10:37.705
But right now, what's happening
in this city right now,

10:37.738 --> 10:40.007
we need to play every card
in the deck.

10:40.040 --> 10:43.443
So bring in Soledad
and her kids, too.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.845
- Tonight?
- It's late,

10:44.878 --> 10:47.748
her kids are asleep.
- Now.

10:50.317 --> 10:52.385
- My children are U.S. citizens.

10:52.419 --> 10:53.954
I have their birth certificates
to prove it.

10:53.987 --> 10:56.690
- And I realize that.
They're safe.

10:56.724 --> 10:58.391
- But you're undocumented,
Soledad.

10:58.425 --> 11:00.293
If we call ICE, game's over.

11:00.327 --> 11:03.330
- I work, I pay taxes,
I've never broken the law.

11:03.363 --> 11:06.033
- You're breaking
the law right now by lying

11:06.066 --> 11:08.702
to protect your husband.
- He didn't kill anybody.

11:08.736 --> 11:09.970
He didn't rape anybody.

11:10.003 --> 11:11.371
You don't have
any evidence on him.

11:11.404 --> 11:12.806
- Is that what
his lawyer told you?

11:12.840 --> 11:17.044
- It's the truth.
- Soledad...

11:17.077 --> 11:21.749
those two beautiful girls
are worth protecting.

11:21.782 --> 11:23.383
They're young, they're innocent,

11:23.416 --> 11:25.753
they have their whole lives
ahead of them.

11:25.786 --> 11:27.955
But your husband
is a different story.

11:27.988 --> 11:31.024
You cannot protect him.

11:31.058 --> 11:33.126
Now, I'm gonna give you
one more chance

11:33.160 --> 11:35.428
to tell me the truth.

11:35.462 --> 11:39.767
Or else I'm gonna have to do
something that...

11:39.800 --> 11:43.771
[sighs]
That I've never done before.

11:43.804 --> 11:45.705
And that's to call ICE.

11:47.808 --> 11:50.878
They're gonna send you back
to El Salvador.

11:50.911 --> 11:55.148
And your daughters
will go to social services.

11:55.182 --> 11:57.350
Listen to me.

11:57.384 --> 12:00.120
I don't wanna do this.

12:00.153 --> 12:02.422
Please give me another option.

12:02.455 --> 12:05.425
[tense music]

12:05.458 --> 12:10.497
*

12:10.530 --> 12:12.099
Okay.

12:12.132 --> 12:19.172
*

12:25.813 --> 12:27.480
This is Lieutenant Benson
from SVU.

12:27.514 --> 12:29.817
I'm calling
for Special Agent Phelps.

12:29.850 --> 12:31.819
Yes, I'll hold.

12:31.852 --> 12:35.555
*

12:35.588 --> 12:36.957
- Phelps.
- Phelps, this is

12:36.990 --> 12:38.558
Lieutenant Benson from SVU.

12:38.591 --> 12:41.962
I had an undocumented female
from El Salvador

12:41.995 --> 12:47.067
who's refusing to cooperate
in a rape/homicide case.

12:47.100 --> 12:48.468
- I'll send
an agent right over.

12:48.501 --> 12:50.470
- Wait, stop!

12:50.503 --> 12:52.405
- Can you hold on a second?

12:52.439 --> 12:54.842
- I'll tell you the truth.

12:54.875 --> 12:57.477
Hector wasn't home.
Not until late.

12:57.510 --> 12:58.812
- What time?

12:58.846 --> 13:01.181
- He woke me up at 2:00 a.m.

13:01.214 --> 13:03.516
He had blood on his shoes.

13:03.550 --> 13:06.186
*

13:06.219 --> 13:08.455
Please, just let me see my kids.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.924
I'll tell you everything.

13:10.958 --> 13:17.931
*

13:17.965 --> 13:19.532
- Yeah.
- She can see her kids.

13:19.566 --> 13:21.068
Go ahead.

13:21.101 --> 13:28.075
*

13:28.108 --> 13:29.509
Agent Phelps?

13:29.542 --> 13:33.981
Yes, the situation
has resolved itself.

13:34.014 --> 13:36.850
Thank you.
I owe you one.

13:36.884 --> 13:39.853
*

13:39.887 --> 13:42.022
- Were you really
gonna go through with it?

13:42.055 --> 13:44.157
Have ICE come snatch her up?

13:44.191 --> 13:50.130
*

13:50.163 --> 13:53.233
- She just boxed Hector
into a corner.

13:53.266 --> 13:57.270
So he has no choice
than to take a deal.

13:59.506 --> 14:02.009
Go pick him up.

14:08.448 --> 14:08.581
.

14:08.615 --> 14:09.249
- Your wife blew up your alibi.

14:11.284 --> 14:12.385
She said you came home
around 2:00 a.m.

14:12.419 --> 14:13.520
and you had blood on your shoes.

14:13.553 --> 14:14.587
- That incriminates you, Hector.

