27:51.303 --> 27:52.772
and we will kill you too."

27:52.805 --> 27:54.707
- So were they ever
wearing masks?

27:54.741 --> 27:56.242
- What do you mean?
- Did you see their faces

27:56.275 --> 27:57.443
the whole time?

27:57.476 --> 27:59.779
Or just for a few seconds?

27:59.812 --> 28:01.781
- They were wearing masks
most of the time

28:01.814 --> 28:04.917
and then they took them off
for a few seconds.

28:04.951 --> 28:06.352
When they threatened me.

28:06.385 --> 28:08.420
- Did Lela see their faces
as well?

28:08.454 --> 28:12.258
- No. It was just me.

28:12.291 --> 28:14.260
I don't care anymore.

28:14.293 --> 28:17.496
Saying nothing isn't helping.

28:17.529 --> 28:19.298
I just want to tell the truth.

28:19.331 --> 28:21.467
And I want to put
these men in prison.

28:21.500 --> 28:24.937
- Okay. As long as
this is the truth.

28:24.971 --> 28:26.806
- This is the truth.

28:28.975 --> 28:30.810
- She's been through hell.
They're filled with rage.

28:30.843 --> 28:32.945
They're doing what
they think is right.

28:32.979 --> 28:34.914
- What does that mean?

28:34.947 --> 28:36.949
- It means I believe
that Maya believes

28:36.983 --> 28:38.751
she saw the faces
of the two perps.

28:38.785 --> 28:40.352
- Do you think that she's
telling the truth?

28:40.386 --> 28:41.888
Yes or no.
- It's not my job

28:41.921 --> 28:43.022
to think or to guess.

28:43.055 --> 28:44.256
It's my job to present evidence

28:44.290 --> 28:45.958
that I believe is credible.

28:45.992 --> 28:47.293
And since we don't have any
proof that Maya is lying,

28:47.326 --> 28:48.895
it's credible.

28:48.928 --> 28:50.296
- So you're gonna
put her on the stand.

28:50.329 --> 28:51.798
- [chuckles]

28:51.831 --> 28:53.766
We both know that victims
and witnesses,

28:53.800 --> 28:55.467
they change their stories,
they change what they recall

28:55.501 --> 28:56.769
all the time.

28:56.803 --> 28:57.770
Her story isn't perfect

28:57.804 --> 28:58.838
but it's plausible.

28:58.871 --> 29:00.439
- Plausible?

29:00.472 --> 29:02.541
So that's the standard.

29:02.574 --> 29:05.511
- At this moment in time, yes.
- [sighs]

29:05.544 --> 29:07.046
- I'm not omniscient, Liv.

29:07.079 --> 29:08.514
I don't have
a judicial crystal ball.

29:08.547 --> 29:10.316
- Nobody wants
these bastards to suffer

29:10.349 --> 29:12.084
more than I do,
believe me, but I--

29:12.118 --> 29:14.553
- Our legal system
is the best that there is.

29:14.586 --> 29:17.556
But it's not perfect.

29:17.589 --> 29:20.492
Or pure.

29:20.526 --> 29:22.028
It never was.

29:26.465 --> 29:28.100
The night of the attack,
did you see the faces

29:28.134 --> 29:30.803
of the men who raped
your daughter Lela,

29:30.837 --> 29:33.272
who raped and killed your
daughter Shala,

29:33.305 --> 29:36.943
who kicked your husband Kanann
in the head?

29:36.976 --> 29:41.080
- Yes. They're right there.

29:41.113 --> 29:43.015
And there was
a third man with them.

29:43.049 --> 29:46.318
Hector Ramirez--he used to
work in the restaurant.

29:46.352 --> 29:47.887
- When you first talked
to the police, did you tell them

29:47.920 --> 29:50.022
that you saw the faces of
the perpetrators?

29:50.056 --> 29:52.024
- No.
- What did you tell them?

29:52.058 --> 29:54.026
- That they were
wearing ski masks.

29:54.060 --> 29:55.294
- Were they wearing ski masks?

29:55.327 --> 29:57.096
- Yes. Most of the time.

29:57.129 --> 30:01.567
But they took them off
when it was all over.

30:01.600 --> 30:04.103
And they threatened me.

30:04.136 --> 30:07.907
They said that they would
kill me and my daughter

30:07.940 --> 30:10.910
if I ever testified
against them.

30:10.943 --> 30:13.412
- What made you
change your mind?

30:13.445 --> 30:14.881
- Anger.

30:17.649 --> 30:21.153
- Can you please explain that?

30:21.187 --> 30:24.456
- My husband is dead.

30:24.490 --> 30:28.060
My daughter Shala is dead.

30:28.094 --> 30:30.596
And my other daughter, Lela...

30:35.935 --> 30:38.404
she's in so much pain.

30:38.437 --> 30:41.173
It's hard for me
to even process.

30:45.511 --> 30:48.380
I don't care if
I live or die anymore.

30:48.414 --> 30:50.849
That is why I decided
to tell the truth.

30:53.652 --> 30:55.854
- Nothing further.

31:02.594 --> 31:05.097
- I can only imagine
how hard this must be for you

31:05.131 --> 31:06.632
and your daughter.

31:06.665 --> 31:11.003
And how confusing it must be.

31:11.037 --> 31:13.572
The morning after the incident,

31:13.605 --> 31:16.142
you told Lieutenant Benson,
quote, you "didn't see

31:16.175 --> 31:17.944
"any of their faces.

31:17.977 --> 31:20.512
They were wearing black ski
masks the whole time."

31:20.546 --> 31:22.148
- That is correct.

31:22.181 --> 31:24.550
- And then the day after
Hector Ramirez was murdered,

31:24.583 --> 31:26.452
you walked into Lieutenant
Benson's office

31:26.485 --> 31:28.154
and you told her
you did see their faces.

31:28.187 --> 31:31.457
That they weren't wearing masks
the whole time.

31:31.490 --> 31:33.993
- Yes.

31:34.026 --> 31:36.595
- So they were wearing masks
the whole time

31:36.628 --> 31:38.597
until Hector Ramirez
was shot and killed.

31:38.630 --> 31:43.402
Then suddenly, they weren't
wearing masks the whole time.

31:43.435 --> 31:45.604
- No. That is not true.
- You knew

31:45.637 --> 31:48.174
the prosecution's case was weak.

31:48.207 --> 31:50.476
You knew that Hector Ramirez
dying made it weaker.

31:50.509 --> 31:52.644
So you decided to lie.
- Objection.

31:52.678 --> 31:55.147
- Sustained.
- You decided

31:55.181 --> 31:57.449
to change your testimony
to increase the odds

31:57.483 --> 31:59.685
of winning the case
and get justice for your family.

31:59.718 --> 32:01.153
- Is there a question here,
anywhere?

32:01.187 --> 32:03.689
- Get to the point, Counselor.

32:03.722 --> 32:06.492
- Isn't it true that you waited
for Hector Ramirez

32:06.525 --> 32:08.660
to be dead before you told
Lieutenant Benson

32:08.694 --> 32:11.463
that you saw the face of
Steven Cole and Mitchell Jenkins

32:11.497 --> 32:13.099
because you believed that was

32:13.132 --> 32:15.067
the only way to win the case?

32:19.105 --> 32:20.572
- No.

32:20.606 --> 32:24.476
That is not true.

32:24.510 --> 32:26.112
I told Lieutenant Benson this

32:26.145 --> 32:30.149
weeks before Hector Ramirez
was killed.

32:30.182 --> 32:33.152
- You told
Lieutenant Benson

32:33.185 --> 32:35.721
weeks before Hector's death?

32:35.754 --> 32:39.158
- Yes.

32:39.191 --> 32:40.959
- Thank you.
Nothing further.

32:45.597 --> 32:48.500
- I believed her until the part
where she said

32:48.534 --> 32:51.203
she called you and made the ID
before Hector got killed.

32:51.237 --> 32:53.272
There's no way that happened.
- That never happened.

32:53.305 --> 32:55.007
- The defense attorney
just totally

32:55.041 --> 32:56.042
backed her into a corner.

32:56.075 --> 32:57.609
What, she got desperate

32:57.643 --> 32:59.645
after all she's been through?
- I guess.

32:59.678 --> 33:02.748
- Liv, you got a sec?

33:02.781 --> 33:04.183
- [sighs]
- I'll see you back

33:04.216 --> 33:06.285
at the squad room.
- Yeah.

33:06.318 --> 33:07.753
- What?
- I just got the updated

33:07.786 --> 33:09.255
witnesses from the defense.

33:09.288 --> 33:11.223
You're on it.
He wants to question you

33:11.257 --> 33:12.558
about the phone call with Maya.
- You mean the phone call

33:12.591 --> 33:14.026
that never happened, right?

33:14.060 --> 33:16.095
You know that never happened.

33:16.128 --> 33:19.031
- If you say so.
- If I say so?

33:19.065 --> 33:20.166
- But--
- What?

33:20.199 --> 33:22.234
- Come here.
- What?

33:22.268 --> 33:24.270
- She has been through
horrific trauma.

33:24.303 --> 33:27.773
Maybe--maybe she forgot the
exact timing of the phone call.

33:27.806 --> 33:30.109
Or the content
of the conversation.

33:30.142 --> 33:32.178
- Are you suggesting
that I back her story?

33:32.211 --> 33:33.612
- I'm suggesting
that she's human.

33:33.645 --> 33:35.314
I'm not telling you
what to say, Liv.

33:35.347 --> 33:38.517
- Really? 'Cause it kinda
sounded like you were.

33:38.550 --> 33:42.288
- This is a different case.
Different circumstances.

33:42.321 --> 33:45.724
[tense music]

33:45.757 --> 33:47.793
You need to do
what you believe is right.

33:47.826 --> 33:49.661
Simple as that.

33:57.603 --> 33:57.769
.

33:57.803 --> 33:58.804
- Okay, Noah, so Lucy's gonna be
here any minute, okay?

34:01.573 --> 34:02.708
What you making there? Oh!
[knock at door]

34:02.741 --> 34:04.210
There she is now!

34:12.584 --> 34:16.288
Chief.
- I was in the neighborhood.

34:16.322 --> 34:19.625
- I didn't know that people
said that anymore.

34:19.658 --> 34:21.760
Come on in.
Can I get you some coffee?

34:21.793 --> 34:23.795
- No, I'm good. I've already had
about five cups.

34:23.829 --> 34:25.397
No wonder
my blood pressure's high.

34:25.431 --> 34:27.833
- So you talked to Barba.

34:27.866 --> 34:31.303
- I did. And I, uh,
I just--

34:31.337 --> 34:33.772
- Look, I don't need advice.

34:33.805 --> 34:36.275
- I'm not here
to give you advice.

34:36.308 --> 34:39.645
- Okay. So why are you here?

34:39.678 --> 34:42.314
- To offer, uh--

34:42.348 --> 34:44.850
absolution.

34:44.883 --> 34:47.319
- Now you're a priest.
- [chuckles]

34:47.353 --> 34:52.291
Look, Liv, there are
no good choices here.

34:52.324 --> 34:54.693
Hey.

34:54.726 --> 34:57.596
But there are
no bad choices, either.

34:57.629 --> 34:59.698
If that makes sense.

34:59.731 --> 35:02.201
- Not really.

35:02.234 --> 35:04.336
- No matter
what decision you make,

35:04.370 --> 35:05.904
you're good.

35:05.937 --> 35:08.740
I'm gonna make sure
your backside's covered.

35:08.774 --> 35:11.243
- I didn't know my backside
needed covering.

35:11.277 --> 35:13.312
- Over the years,

35:13.345 --> 35:15.614
I've been in this situation.

35:15.647 --> 35:18.417
A few times, myself.

35:18.450 --> 35:21.387
- And?
- And I played it both ways.

35:21.420 --> 35:23.322
I've forgotten certain
things that helped get

35:23.355 --> 35:26.192
the right result and I've
remembered certain things

35:26.225 --> 35:30.762
that helped get
the wrong result.

35:30.796 --> 35:34.900
God's honest truth?
It feels the same.

35:34.933 --> 35:39.905
But that's me. I'm good at
rationalizing things.

35:39.938 --> 35:42.341
Comes with the territory,
I suppose.

35:45.411 --> 35:47.946
- What would you have told Mike?

35:47.979 --> 35:50.949
[tense music]

35:50.982 --> 35:52.951
*

35:52.984 --> 35:55.321
- Same thing I just told you.

35:55.354 --> 36:02.394
*

36:05.264 --> 36:07.666
- When was the first time you
talked with Maya Samra?

36:07.699 --> 36:10.902
- The morning after the double
rape, double homicide.

36:10.936 --> 36:12.871
Inside her restaurant.

36:12.904 --> 36:14.873
- Did you ask her if she saw
the faces of the intruders?

36:14.906 --> 36:17.209
- Yes, I did.
- What did she say?

36:17.243 --> 36:19.711
- She said that they were
wearing ski masks.

36:19.745 --> 36:21.680
- The whole time?

36:21.713 --> 36:23.949
- Yes.
- Mm.

36:23.982 --> 36:26.718
Did Mrs. Samra
ever change her story

36:26.752 --> 36:32.424
as it relates to seeing the
actual faces of the intruders?

36:32.458 --> 36:38.430
- Yes.
- When?

36:38.464 --> 36:41.400
- A week after.
- [scoffs]

36:41.433 --> 36:43.835
Was this before or after

36:43.869 --> 36:46.805
Hector Ramirez
was shot to death?

36:46.838 --> 36:48.840
- After.
- So Mrs. Samra's

36:48.874 --> 36:50.942
version of events
is different than yours?

36:50.976 --> 36:53.445
- Yes, but often victims of
this kind of trauma have--

36:53.479 --> 36:56.382
- Her version is different,
so she's lying.

36:56.415 --> 36:58.317
- Objection.
- Sustained.

36:58.350 --> 37:01.853
The jury will disregard
that comment.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.755
- Nothing further.

37:03.789 --> 37:10.829
*

37:13.599 --> 37:15.334
- You said you would help us.

37:15.367 --> 37:16.868
You said that
you are on our side.

37:16.902 --> 37:18.304
That you would
help us get justice.

37:18.337 --> 37:19.538
- I'm so sorry, Maya.

37:19.571 --> 37:21.273
- You said that you care.

37:21.307 --> 37:22.874
You don't even care.
- That's not true.

37:22.908 --> 37:24.476
- I give you a chance
right there,

37:24.510 --> 37:25.944
right now,
and you didn't take it.

37:25.977 --> 37:27.346
You didn't take
your chance to help

37:27.379 --> 37:29.281
and now the men are free.

37:29.315 --> 37:30.849
Those men who destroyed
my family,

37:30.882 --> 37:32.318
those men who destroyed my life.
- It's okay.

37:32.351 --> 37:33.885
We will be okay.

37:33.919 --> 37:35.521
We will be okay.

37:37.923 --> 37:40.992
- [sighs]
Oh, my God.

37:41.026 --> 37:42.994
- They're angry at you?

37:43.028 --> 37:46.031
- [sighs]
Yes.

37:46.064 --> 37:47.599
- Because you didn't
back up her story

37:47.633 --> 37:49.301
about seeing my husband's face?

37:49.335 --> 37:53.872
- It doesn't matter what
I did or didn't say.

37:53.905 --> 37:56.475
Your husband is guilty.

37:56.508 --> 37:59.545
- I know what they did.

37:59.578 --> 38:04.015
- Well, then
do something about it.

38:04.049 --> 38:06.051
I know that
you called the police

38:06.084 --> 38:08.520
four times
in the last two years.

38:08.554 --> 38:10.522
I know that you know

38:10.556 --> 38:12.624
what kind of man he is.

38:12.658 --> 38:16.061
What kind of violence
he's capable of.

38:16.094 --> 38:18.630
- He's my husband.
- He's a rapist

38:18.664 --> 38:20.499
and a murderer.

38:20.532 --> 38:24.370
And the next dead woman
on the floor...

38:24.403 --> 38:26.405
that might be you.

38:29.975 --> 38:35.414
So don't tell the truth
for Maya or for Lela.

38:35.447 --> 38:39.317
Tell the truth for yourself
and for your son.

38:42.554 --> 38:45.924
Take that first step.

38:45.957 --> 38:48.427
- Towards what?

38:48.460 --> 38:51.397
- Freedom.

38:51.430 --> 38:53.365
Safety.

38:53.399 --> 39:00.439
*

39:03.609 --> 39:06.578
- The night the Samra family was
attacked, what were you doing?

39:06.612 --> 39:09.515
- Watching TV.
- Who were you with?

39:09.548 --> 39:12.618
- My son.
- Was your husband with you

39:12.651 --> 39:14.019
that evening?

39:18.690 --> 39:22.994
- [sighs]
No.

39:23.028 --> 39:25.397
- When you spoke to the police
after your husband

39:25.431 --> 39:28.567
was arrested, you stated that
you and your husband were home

39:28.600 --> 39:30.001
the entire evening.

39:30.035 --> 39:31.503
That you made dinner;
you watched TV.

39:31.537 --> 39:34.440
You were in bed by
approximately 10:00 p.m.

39:34.473 --> 39:37.643
- I was lying.
- Sorry.

39:37.676 --> 39:41.146
You were lying?

39:41.179 --> 39:43.915
- Yes.

39:43.949 --> 39:46.452
- Then or now?

39:46.485 --> 39:49.187
- Then.

39:49.220 --> 39:51.490
Today, I'm telling the truth.

39:51.523 --> 39:54.460
I didn't see him that night
until early in the morning

39:54.493 --> 39:56.628
and he had blood
on his pants and shoes.

39:56.662 --> 39:57.629
- You lying bitch.

39:57.663 --> 39:58.930
- Sit down!

39:58.964 --> 40:00.165
Order.
Restrain him.

40:00.198 --> 40:01.199
- I'll kill you!
- Remove him!

40:01.232 --> 40:02.601
[overlapping chatter]

40:02.634 --> 40:04.903
Let me go!
You're dead, Carleen!

40:04.936 --> 40:07.906
Dead! You heard me!

40:07.939 --> 40:09.975
- Order.
[overlapping chatter]

40:10.008 --> 40:16.982
*

40:17.015 --> 40:19.951
- Today, justice was served.
[cheering]

40:19.985 --> 40:23.522
Just--well, this victory
will not bring back

40:23.555 --> 40:25.624
Shala and Kanann Samra.

40:25.657 --> 40:29.928
Or erase the tragic events
of this crime.

40:29.961 --> 40:33.632
It may help the Samra family
and this great city

40:33.665 --> 40:35.967
begin to heal.

40:36.001 --> 40:37.168
- Boo! Boo!
- Mr. Barba!

40:37.202 --> 40:39.070
- Excuse me.

40:39.104 --> 40:43.208
[crowd chatter]
Thank you, no, no comment.

40:43.241 --> 40:45.744
- A hell of a case.

40:45.777 --> 40:47.513
- Hell of a year.

40:47.546 --> 40:51.116
- We got the conviction.
That's all that matters.

40:51.149 --> 40:54.553
- Wish it was that simple.

40:54.586 --> 40:56.655
- See you tomorrow, Liv.
- See you guys.

41:03.695 --> 41:06.164
- Hey.
- Hey.

41:06.197 --> 41:09.067
- Buy you
a celebratory cocktail?

41:09.100 --> 41:11.970
- No, thanks,
I have to get home.

41:12.003 --> 41:14.540
- Right.
Are you upset with me?

41:14.573 --> 41:17.175
- No.
- Disenchanted?

41:20.746 --> 41:24.182
- We all have to answer
to our own gods.

41:24.215 --> 41:27.118
- Luckily mine is a little bit
more accepting than yours.

41:30.055 --> 41:31.757
[knocking]

41:31.790 --> 41:35.193
- Sorry to interrupt.
- Chief.

41:35.226 --> 41:38.797
What's going on?
Is everything okay?

41:38.830 --> 41:43.769
- A mosque in East Harlem
just got firebombed.

41:43.802 --> 41:45.236
Five dead.

42:09.127 --> 42:12.097
[dramatic music]

42:12.130 --> 42:19.170
*

42:37.355 --> 42:40.558
[wolf howls]
